      "title": "ℹ️ About — BrainDead Channel Operations",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# 🧠 BrainDead — Channel Operations\n\nThree nodes for packing, unpacking, and merging image channels. Essential for PBR map creation, mask-to-channel workflows, and RGBA compositing.\n\n## BD_UnpackChannels\nSplits any image into its R, G, B, A channels — as both `IMAGE` (greyscale preview) and `MASK` (float tensor). The `debug_preview` output shows all 4 channels as a 2×2 grid.\n\n**Use when:** You need individual channels from a packed ORM texture, or want to use one channel of an image as a mask for BD_PackChannels.\n\n## BD_PackChannels\nBuilds a new image where each channel (R/G/B/A) can come from:\n- An **IMAGE** (luminance extracted via luma standard)\n- A **MASK** (used directly as the channel value)\n- A **default float** (constant fill: 0.0 = black, 1.0 = white)\n\nThe `debug_preview` output shows the resulting R, G, B, A as a 2×2 grid.\n\n**Use when:** Creating ORM maps (Occlusion/Roughness/Metallic), skin shader channel maps, or any custom multi-channel texture from separate greyscale sources.\n\n**Example ORM setup:**\n```\nRed   ← AO mask or image\nGreen ← Roughness mask or image\nBlue  ← Metallic mask or image\nAlpha ← default 1.0\n```\n\n## BD_ChannelMerge\nCopies channel data **from** a source image **into** specific channels of a base image. Source can be a single channel (R/G/B/A) or computed luminance.\n\n**target_channels:** which channel(s) to write into (R, G, B, A, RG, RGB, RGBA…)\n**source_from:** how to extract from source (luma_bt709, channel_R, channel_G…)\n**blend_mode:** replace / add / multiply / screen / overlay / etc.\n\n**Use when:** Injecting a roughness map into the green channel of an existing texture, or baking an AO pass into the red channel without recreating the whole image.\n\n## This Workflow\nRound-trip: **Unpack** an image → extract R/G/B as masks → **Pack** them back → **Merge** the result into the original's R channel.\n\n---\n**BrainDeadGuild** — created by **BizaNator**\n[BrainDeadGuild.com](https://BrainDeadGuild.com) · [BrainDead.TV](https://BrainDead.TV) · [GitHub](https://github.com/BizaNator/ComfyUI-BrainDead) · [Discord](https://braindeadguild.com/discord)\n"
      ]
    },
